# Sprint 3.1 – Phase 2: Security Layer Implementation Plan

This implementation plan covers the design and delivery of the production-quality **Security Layer** for the AlgoPath application. It introduces two independent, stateless service classes for password security and JWT management under `backend/app/services/`.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Existing `auth_service.py` Conflict**
> There is an existing [auth_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/auth_service.py) in the codebase that implements simple hashing and token creation using standard module-level functions.
>
> In alignment with the requirements ("Do not implement login or registration. Do not access SQLAlchemy models. Do not implement authentication routes"), we will create the two new independent services:
> - `PasswordService` in [password_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/password_service.py)
> - `JWTService` in [jwt_service.py](file:///d:/Projects/Antigravity/project%201/project%201.1/backend/app/services/jwt_service.py)
>
> These services will **not** initially replace the existing `auth_service.py` to prevent breaking other parts of the application. The migration of `auth_service.py` to use these new services is proposed as a follow-up step.

